help him with these calculations.  When Henry coompares the total cost
to the money he has on hand, he'll undoubtedly come up short.  But
there are ways he can handle this deficit:

2nd column	4th paragraph
NEXT YEAR, REMIND HENRY TO GO THROUGH THESE STEPS EARLY IN NOVEMBER.
Then he'll have more time to budget his finances, make things or earn
extra money before he needs to shop.
